      "writtenOn": "2018-02-15T23:46:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Actually a lot.  Filtering by structured JSON data has first class support in stackdriver, and it\u0027s the recommended way to do things as per:\nhttps://cloud.google.com/kubernetes-engine/docs/how-to/logging\n\nUsing this, i can filter by message ID explicitly, for instance:\nhttps://pantheon.corp.google.com/logs/viewer?project\u003dluci-logdog-dev\u0026resource\u003dcontainer%2Fcluster_name%2Flogdog-archivist-v2%2Fnamespace_id%2Fdefault\u0026minLogLevel\u003d0\u0026expandAll\u003dfalse\u0026timestamp\u003d2018-02-15T23:20:31.577337340Z\u0026dateRangeStart\u003d2018-02-15T22:20:51.643Z\u0026dateRangeEnd\u003d2018-02-15T23:20:51.643Z\u0026interval\u003dPT1H\u0026advancedFilter\u003dresource.type%3D%22container%22%0Aresource.labels.cluster_name%3D%22logdog-archivist-v2%22%0Aresource.labels.namespace_id%3D%22default%22%0AjsonPayload.fields.messageID%3D%2235635794094946%22",
      "parentUuid": "e78d07f9_92068491",
